==Translingual==
===Etymology===
From ''p'', denoting negative logarithm, and ''H'', denoting hydrogen.

===Noun===
{{en-noun|pH|pHs}}

#{{abbreviation}} The negative of the [[logarithm]] to the base 10 of the concentration of [[hydrogen]] ions, measured in [[mole]]s per liter; a measure of acidity or alkalinity of a substance, which takes numerical values from 0 (maximum acidity) through 7 (neutral) to 14 (maximum alkalinity).

